impactText:
  The partner organisation (Anglian Water Services) has benefitted from the research in several ways:
(1) Their household micro-component water use data set has been quality assured and cleansed;
(2) The strengths and limitations of their survey data are now better understood (from point of collection to synthesis into summary statistics on per capita water demand);
(3) The relative significance of weather, socio-economic and behavioural drivers of household water use in Eastern England are now better understood by AWS;
(4) Specific insights have been gained into the impact of a hosepipe ban on customer behaviour during the 2012 drought (and subsequent switch to very wet summer conditions). Environment,Other Economic
